kg.Trainmaster Command Control: {"TrainmasterCommand": {"name": "Trainmaster Command","abbreviation": "TMCC","description": {"Lionel's electronic control system": {"for": "O scale 3-rail model trains and toy trains","running from": "1994 to 2006"}},"similarityToDCC": "Conceptually similar to Digital Command Control (DCC), the industry's open standard used by HO scale and other 2-rail DC trains.","advantageOverDCC": "TMCC-equipped locomotives can run simultaneously with non-TMCC locomotives and Lionel Legacy engines as well as LionChief and LionChief Plus equipped locomotives.","advantageDescription": "TMCC-equipped locomotives can run simultaneously with non-TMCC locomotives and Lionel Legacy engines as well as LionChief and LionChief Plus equipped locomotives.","compatibleWith": ["Lionel Legacy engines", "LionChief-equipped locomotives", "LionChief Plus-equipped locomotives", "MTH Corporation's DCS controller"],"compatibilityDescription": "MTH Corporation's DCS controller can be configured to control TMCC locomotives, and all four systems (TMCC, Legacy, LionChief/LionChief+, and DCS) can be operated on the same track simultaneously.","powerRequirement": "Each simply requires a constant track voltage (18 volts).","operationDescription": "TMCC/Legacy 'broadcasts' its signal to the antenna on the locomotives which listen for signals that first identify the particular locomotive by number and then issue given commands as to speed, direction, sounds, lighting, and other features.","DCSOperationDescription": "DCS performs similar functions but transmits a carrier over the rails which are picked up through the locomotive's electrical pickup contacts.","LionChiefOperationDescription": "LionChief/LionChief+ also issue remote control commands, but the remote and locomotive are married, and each locomotive requires a separate remote control. This system requires no additional wiring as the control is directly 'narrowcast' to the locomotive.","universalRemoteReleaseYear": 2017,"universalRemoteDescription": "In 2017, Lionel released a universal remote for LionChief+ that will learn addresses for up to three locos at a time, simplifying the operation of multiple trains."}}
